data.name: AMAT
data.description: Home of the Aerocapture Mission Analysis Tool (AMAT). For project documentation visit:

evidence: README install command: "* ```$ pip install AMAT```"

"AMAT was developed at the Advanced Astrodynamics Concepts (AAC) research group at Purdue University." and later: "If you wish to contribute or report an issue, feel free to contact me (mailto:athulpg007@gmail.com)" – indicates a primarily individual-maintained project in a research context, owned by user account athulpg007.

"Aerocapture Mission Analysis Tool (AMAT) is designed to provide rapid mission analysis capability for aerocapture and atmospheric Entry, Descent, and Landing (EDL) mission concepts" and "AMAT allows the user to simulate atmospheric entry trajectories, compute deceleration and heating loads..." – users run it to perform domain analyses, i.e., an application.
